-- Full-Year Loss at Opel Is Lower Than GM Expected, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   O l i v e r   S u e s s
-- 2010-10-14T05:07:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/full-year-loss-at-opel-is-lower-than-gm-expected-handelsblatt-reports.html
General Motors Co. ’s Adam Opel unit
recorded a lower than anticipated full-year loss,  Handelsblatt 
reported, citing Opel’s annual statement, which it obtained.  Opel lost 427 million euros ($601 million) in 2009 compared
to a forecast operating loss of 1.2 billion euros, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
